{"word":"ἄπλοος","slug":"ἄπλοος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄπλοος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πλέω'><el>πλέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a>, of ships, <i>not sailing, unfit for sea, not sea-worthy</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a>, <el>ἀπλοώτεραι ναῦς</el> <i>less fit for sea</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a>, of the sea, <i>not navigable</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}